snippet.title: Atari Collection 2 - Evercade Cartridge Tour
snippet.description:
Captured off of the Original Evercade handheld. This cart contains 20 more games from both the Atari 2600 and 7800.

Games in the cart:
00:08 - Air-Sea Battle (2600) [Release date is 1977, not 1997]
02:26 - Asteroids (7800)
04:25 - Basketbrawl (7800)
06:12 - Bowling (2600)
08:44 - Centipede (7800)
10:21 - Dark Chambers (2600)
14:57 - Demons To Diamonds (2600)
18:09 - Desert Falcon (7800)
20:04 - Haunted House (2600)
22:56 - Human Cannonball (2600)
25:13 - Millipede (2600)
27:02 - Planet Smashers (7800)
29:39 - Radar Lock (2600)
33:00 - RealSports Tennis (2600)
34:45 - Solaris (2600)
38:08 - Sprint Master (2600)
40:41 - Street Racer (2600)
44:26 - Submarine Commander (2600)
47:15 - Wizard (2600)*
49:30 - Yars' Revenge (2600)

*An unreleased prototype. It was officially released as part of the Atari Flashback 2 microconsole.
